{
  "schema_version": "1.0",
  "name": "7-Segment Up/Down Counter",
  "description": "BCD up/down counter driving 7-segment display. NE555 astable provides clock. 74HC192 counts up or down on separate clock inputs. CD4511 decodes BCD to 7-segment. Common cathode display. SW1=count up, SW2=count down, SW3=reset.",
  "notes": "PARTS TO ACQUIRE: 74HC192 (BCD up/down counter), CD4511 (BCD to 7-seg decoder/driver), common cathode 7-segment display. All available on AliExpress/eBay. 74HC192: CU=pin5 (up clock), CD=pin4 (down clock), MR=pin14 (reset, active high), Q outputs → 4511 inputs. CD4511: LE=pin5 low (transparent), LT=pin3 high (no lamp test), BI=pin4 high (no blank). R1-R7=330Ω segment resistors. NE555 astable at ~1Hz provides visible count clock.",
